                <h1>Understanding "The Yellow Wallpaper" Through First-Person Perspective</h1>
                <p>The yellow wallpaper is narrated from a first-person point of view, allowing readers to intimately experience the protagonist's descent into madness. This perspective immerses us in her conflicted emotions and isolation in a rented mansion. The vibrant wallpaper becomes a symbol of her entrapment, reflecting her struggle for identity and freedom.</p>
